    • Method Detail

      • getLogMessage

        java.lang.String getLogMessage()
        The message to log.

      • getLogMessageDescription

        java.lang.String getLogMessageDescription()
        Optional. Additional details associated with the message. In many logs, this appears as an additional descriptive line in log output. This may be null or an empty string, and should be ignored if it is such.

      • getLogMessageType

        int getLogMessageType()
        The type of the message to log. For example, a GENERIC message, a PASSED message, a FAILED message, etc.. This may be implementation specific.
